headline: Qualcomm & McDonald's earnings, ADP job data: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Wednesday, Nov. 5. New York City's mayoral race is underway, with polls to close at 9:00 p.m. on Tuesday. Toyota (TM), Novo Nordisk (NVO), and McDonald's (MCD) will report quarterly earnings before the opening bell, while AppLovin (APP), Qualcomm (QCOM), and Robinhood (HOOD) report after the closing bell. ADP (ADP) will release employment data for October. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: AppLovin jumps after strong Q3 earnings and upbeat Q4 outlook
summary: Investing.com -- Applovin Corp (NASDAQ:APP) shares edged up nearly 3% in after-hours trading Wednesday, following third-quarter earnings that topped Wall Street forecasts and a bullish revenue outlook for the final stretch of the year. The digital marketing firm reported strong growth in both its software platform and apps segments, continuing its momentum amid structural shifts in mobile advertising.

headline: AppLovin Reports Strong Earnings. The Stock Is Up.
